18/10/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Troops killed three leftist extremists in eastern Turkey, the government reported Monday (17 October). The three, identified as members of the Maoist Communist Party-People's Liberation Army, died in a gun battle near the village of Gozeler in the province of Tunceli during an army operation against the terrorist Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK). 
Also Monday, the PKK claimed responsibility for the bombing of a gas station in Istanbul. Five people were injured in the Sunday blast. (Reuters, AFP - 17/10/05)
